agent.housing experience: I’ve lived at the same address on 15th Avenue in the Sunset District, where my family has been rooted for generations. The house was originally my grandparents’, passed down to my parents, and now I help take care of it. We haven’t moved, but we’ve definitely felt the pressure — rising property taxes, new development creeping in, and the change in character of the neighborhood. What used to be a quiet, mostly family-filled area is seeing more dense apartment buildings and tech folks moving in. It’s still home, but it’s not the same Sunset I grew up in.
